   <head>Poesie latine - III</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1">
     <l n="1">Iam sileat iactare fidem flammasque Saguntum, </l>
     <l n="2">
Massilia obsidium, moenia hetrusca famem. </l>
     <l n="3">
Caesareis nam sponte sua fidissima signis, </l>
     <l n="4">
Parthenope his voluit horridiora pati. </l>
     <l n="5">
Plaude tamen, quoniam datur, ut si barbara castra</l>
     <l n="6">
te lacerent semper, semper humare tuum est. </l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
